# Project Structure

This project uses a **feature-based architecture**.  
Each business domain is organized inside the `features/` directory.

Next.js routing still lives inside `app/`, but **pages should only import logic from features**.

```
app/                  → Next.js App Router (routing layer only)
  (auth)/             → Authentication pages
    auth/             → Login, Register, Forgot Password, Reset Password pages
  (public)/           → Public pages
    page.tsx          → Home page
    about-us/         → About us page
    faq/              → FAQ page
    pricing/          → Pricing page
    contact-us/       → Contact us page

  (protected)/        → Authenticated application
    dashboard/        → Main application
      [feature]/page.tsx → Feature route page  (route only,server component, do not "use client")
  api/                → API routes
  docs/               → Documentation pages

features/             → Business features directory
  [feature-name]/     → Feature directory (e.g. materials, vendors, uoms)
    actions/          → contains server actions and mutation entry points for the feature
    components/       → contains feature-owned presentation components and UI blocks
    hooks/            → contains reusable feature-scoped hooks for UI behavior and state handling
    repositories/     → contains data access logic and persistence queries for the feature
    services/         → contains use cases, orchestration, and business rules for the feature
    schemas/          → contains validation schemas for inputs, forms, filters, and requests
    table/            → contains TanStack Table configuration and table-specific UI for the feature
    types/            → contains TypeScript types and interfaces owned by the feature
    constants/        → contains feature-scoped constants, enums, and static configuration values
    index.ts          → contains the public export surface for the feature

components/           → Reusable React components
  data-table/         → Data table shared components (e.g. DataTable.tsx, TableContainer.tsx, TableViewOptions.tsx, etc.)
  form/               → Form shared components (e.g. TextField.tsx, SelectField.tsx, TextareaField.tsx, etc.)
  ui/                 → UI shared components (e.g. button.tsx, input.tsx, select.tsx, etc.)
  navbar/             → Navbar components
  footer/             → Footer components

config/               → Application configuration
  app.config.ts       → App name, description, URLs
  storage.config.ts   → File upload settings

lib/                  → Core utilities
  prisma.ts           → Prisma client & helpers
  utils.ts            → Utility functions
  auth.ts             → Auth utilities
  auth-client.ts      → Auth client utilities

prisma/               → Prisma ORM
  schema.prisma       → Database schema (models, enums, relations)
  migrations/         → SQL migrations
  seeders/            → Seeders for the database
```
